## Code Example

```javascript
module.exports = async function(context, blob) {
  const name = context.bindingData.name; // e.g. tenants/{tenant}/source/{file}
  const parts = name.split('/');
  const tenantId = parts[1];
  const fileName = parts[3];

  // Idempotency check
  const thumbnailPath = `tenants/${tenantId}/thumbnails/${fileName}`;

  try {
    // Resize with sharp
    const sharp = require('sharp');
    const thumbnail = await sharp(blob).resize(300, 300).toBuffer();

    // Save thumbnail
    context.bindings.outputBlob = thumbnail;

    // Audit entry
    context.bindings.auditTable = {
      PartitionKey: tenantId,
      RowKey: `${Date.now()}-${fileName}`,
      Timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),
      Status: 'processed'
    };

  } catch (error) {
    // Dead-letter on failure
    context.bindings.deadLetterQueue = {
      tenantId,
      fileName,
      error: error.message,
      timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
    };
    throw error;
  }
};
```

## End-to-End Flow

1. User uploads image to `tenants/{tenantId}/source/{filename}`
2. Event Grid emits BlobCreated event
3. Azure Function triggers, extracts tenantId from path
4. Function resizes image to 300x300 using sharp
5. Thumbnail saved to `tenants/{tenantId}/thumbnails/{filename}`
6. Audit entry logged with tenantId as PartitionKey
7. On failure, message sent to dead-letter queue for retry

